SherlockHolmesComplete_201303.title: The Complete Sherlock Holmes
description:
The following is a collection of all the Sherlock Holmes novels by Sir Arthur Conan Doyle. These novels follow the adventures of the world's greatest detective, Sherlock Holmes and his friend and assistant, Dr. John Watson. Over the course of the novels, Holmes uses his above-average observation skills to solve crimes. But when Holmes and Watson come up against Professor Moriarty, a worthy but villainous opponent, will Holmes' intellect be enough to save them?

Recommended Titles Include:
A Study In Scarlet (Holmes and Watson first meet and try to catch a serial killer)
A Scandal in Bohemia (Holmes finds an equal in Irene Adler, who proves to be almost as clever as him)
The Hound of the Baskervilles (Holmes and Watson travel to the country where the family Baskerville is being haunted by a spectral hound)
The Final Problem (Holmes goes up against his most dangerous opponent, Professor Moriarty. Will his wit be enough to save him?)

Suggested Reading Level: US (Upper Secondary) OR UG (Undergraduate)

QuellePorcherie.title: Quelle porcherie!
description:
Synopsis: Franklin's family lives in, well, a pigsty. As a meticulously neat piglet, Franklin finds his family's slovenly ways a great embarrassment, and he dares not encourage visitors. At school, his brothers' unruly antics further humiliate him. All this changes when Franklin wins first prize for his painting of a rainbow. His father chooses the perfect spot to hang the picture, but Franklin asks him if he could first wash the wall. The entire family dives into a housecleaning spree and the result is a home worthy of Franklin's masterpiece. Friends even visit, and the family enjoys staying clean (except for an occasional mud bath). Wilhelm's book plunges right to the center of the concerns of children who sometimes feel like the odd member out among the people in their families. His text and watercolors capture the charms of this porcine clan both before and after their radical reformation. (From "Publishers Weekly").

(Franklin est le seul cochon propre de sa famille. Il n'ose pas inviter ses amis chez lui. Après avoir peint un très beau dessin, sa famille décide de se faire belle et de nettoyer la maison pour donner une place parfaite à ce dessin.) 

Suggested level: EE, LP

NorthSouth.title: North & South
description:
North & South is a prime example of a social protest novel, or a novel written to bring to light certain social issues that were going unnoticed. The story follows Margaret Hale, a clergyman's daughter forced into destitution. Upon moving from the south of England to the north (an area famed for its industrial development), she must deal with the major social and class differences between the two. The novel also follows the story of the family Higgins, a working class family dealing with the consequences of unionization and a mass industrial strike. 

Suggested Level: US (Upper Secondary)

subject: Music
28LikeARollingStoneLiveVersion320LameCbr.author: Dylan, Bob
description:
Bob Dylan is an American singer-songwriter who rose to prominence in the 1960s thanks to his folk songs (many of which have themes of social protest).  He later reacted against the acoustic folk movement by "plugging in", employing electric guitar and a full band in his recordings.  His influence on many key artists in rock music (examples include John Lennon, Patti Smith, and Bruce Springsteen) has earned him special awards from U.S. President Barack Obama and the Pulitzer Prize Committee, among others.

All of the songs included in this collection were written by Dylan.  Four of these recordings ("Blowin' in the Wind", "Masters of War", and "With God On Our Side") are performed by Dylan himself.  "A Hard Rain's A-Gonna Fall" is performed by Texas-based folk duo Carrie Elkin and Danny Schmidt, while "The Times They Are A-Changin'" is performed by contemporary roots-rock band Of A Revolution (better known as O.A.R.).

This collection includes a classroom activity related to the song "Blowin' in the Wind."

GirlRisingInNepalAGirlAWriterAPowerfulSt.filename: /GirlRisingInNepalAGirlAWriterAPowerfulStory..thumbs/Girl Rising in Nepal_ a girl, a writer, a powerful story._001050.jpg
description:
Girl Rising is a film about the strength of the human spirit and the power of education to change the world. Here, watch Suma's story of being bonded into labor at age 6 and how she now uses her hard-won education to help free other girls. Meet acclaimed author Manjushree Thapa who wrote Suma's story for the film, and learn about the devastating practice of "kamlari," or bonded labor that is, in effect, modern day slavery.

Suggested Level: LP (Lower Primary)

SelectMusicOfJoanBaez.author: Baez, Joan
SelectMusicOfJoanBaez.filename: /Joan Baez - House of the Rising Sun.mp3
description:
Joan Baez (1941- ) is an American folk singer, songwriter, musician, and social activist.  Her work includes original compositions and covers of both traditional and contemporary songs.  She continues to perform--and to speak out for social justice--to this day.

This collection includes "House of the Rising Sun" and "The House Carpenter", two traditional ballads.  "Ruby Tuesday" was originally written by Mick Jagger and Keith Richards of rock group The Rolling Stones, and "There But For Fortune" is the composition of fellow American protest singer Phil Ochs.

description:
Synopsis: Voltaire publie en 1759 Candide, un conte philosophique allègre et critique. Pour avoir embrassé l'appétissante Cunégonde, le jeune Candide est chassé du château du baron de Thunder-ten-tronckh à coups de pied dans le derrière. Commence alors pour lui un grand voyage qui lui fait découvrir les horreurs du monde.

(Witty and caustic, Candide has ranked as one of the world's great satires since its first publication in 1759. In the story of the trials and travails of the youthful Candide, his mentor Dr. Pangloss, and a host of other characters, Voltaire mercilessly satirizes and exposes romance, science, philosophy, religion, and government – from Amazon.)

BlueSuedeShoes_201307.author: Presley, Elvis
description:
Elvis Presley (1935-1977) was an American musician whose heyday was in the 1950s and 1960s.  The singer-guitarist's passionately performed tunes and outrageous dancing made him a hit with the youth as well as the object of parental disapproval.  While the moral panic eventually faded, Elvis's legacy did not, and he is still celebrated today as "The King" of rock and roll.

This sampler includes the following (all songs performed by Elvis and credited to their composers):
Blue Suede Shoes (Carl Perkins)
Love Me Tender (adapted from a song by George R. Poulton)
Hound Dog (Jerry Leiber and Mike Stoller)
Jailhouse Rock (Jerry Leiber and Mike Stoller)
Can't Help Falling In Love (Hugo Peretti, Luigi Creatore, George David Weiss)

207YouCantAlwaysGetWhatYouWant.author: The Rolling Stones
description:
The Rolling Stones (1962-present) are a British rock band famous for songs like Sympathy for the Devil, Gimme Shelter and You Can't Always Get What You Want. The band is mainly based in rhythm and blues, but is also a symbol of rebellion to many oppressed youths. They were inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in 1989 and they are widely thought to be one of the best bands of all time.

Songs included in this collection are:
You Can't Always Get What You Want
Jumping Jack Flash
Beast of Burden
Honky Tonk Woman
Sympathy for the Devil

Suggested Level: US (Upper Secondary)

JimiHendrixAllAlongTheWatchtower.author: Hendrix, Jimi
description:
Jimi Hendrix (1942-1970) was an American rock guitarist and the leader of The Jimi Hendrix Experience and Band of Gypsies, two musical groups of the 1960s.  Although his music was famous for only a few years before his untimely death, Hendrix is considered to be one of the most important electric guitarists of the 20th century.

This collection includes:
All Along the Watchtower (original song by Bob Dylan)
Fire
Little Wing
Purple Haze
The United States National Anthem (original tune by John Stafford Smith)
This collection includes a video file of the Hendrix original The Wind Cries Mary and a PDF file of a related classroom activity on literary devices, courtesy of the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame website.

subject: Music
08BehindBlueEyes.author: The Who
description:
The Who (1964-1982) is an English rock band famous for songs like Pinball Wizard, My Generation and Behind Blue Eyes; however less known songs like I Don't Even Know Myself really speak to what the band was about. They were able to capture the change in culture between the 50's morals to 60's lack thereof; a time that left a whole generation unsure about where they fit in to the grander scheme of things. Their sound was also highly transitional. The band combined Rhythm and Blues with Rock, Pop and Punk into a sound that was unique to them.

They sold over 100 million records, released 27 hit singles and had 18 Gold Albums. The band was a major influence for artists like Led Zepplin and The Clash. In 1990, they were inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame. Many consider them to be one of the best and most influential bands of all time.

Included in this collection are the following songs:
Behind Blue Eyes
Won't Get Fooled Again
I Don't Even Know Myself
My Generation
Overture
It's a Boy
1921
Amazing Journey
Sparks
The Hawker
Christmas
Cousin Kevin
The Acid Queen
Underture
Do You Think It's Alright?
Fiddle About
Pinball Wizard
There's a Doctor
Go to the Mirror
Tommy Can You Hear Me?
Smash the Mirror
Sensation
Miracle Cure
Sally Sampson
I'm Free
Welcome
Tommy's Holiday Camp
We're Not Gonna Take It

Suggested Level: LS (Lower Secondary) OR US (Upper Secondary)

Lfdrm10a.author: Pedro Calderón de la Barca
description:
A king produces an heir to his throne, but on the day of his birth a prophet informs him that his son will be an evil, wicked ruler. So the king locks his son away in a tower for his entire life and he learns nothing of the outside world. But when the king finds out that he can no longer have children, he decides that his only living heir is his only hope for a legacy.
So, the king decides that he will let his son be king for the day, telling him that his entire life in the tower has been a dream.
A story about the meaning of life, the meaning of reality and the very nature of a human soul.
NOTE: This text will require time and attention, it is not for the casual reader.
Suggested Reading Level: UG (Undergrad)
Lfdrm10a.title: Life is a Dream

description: Bobby Darin (1936-1973) was an American singer and songwriter. He is best known for singing American classics. However, towards the end of his life, Darin switched from songs about love to songs about politics. Darin was an outspoken advocate for peace and against United States involvement in Vietnam. In 1990, he was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame and in 1999 into the Songwriters Hall of Fame.
